The global canola protein market is expected to witness significant growth by 2028. The market is segmented by type into hydrolyzed canola protein, isolated canola protein, and concentrated canola protein. Increasing awareness regarding the health benefits of canola protein, such as its high protein content and low allergenic properties, is driving the market growth. By application, the market is segmented into functional foods & beverages, animal feed, and pharmaceuticals. The functional foods & beverages segment is anticipated to dominate the market due to the rising adoption of plant-based proteins in the food industry. Moreover, the animal feed segment is projected to witness substantial growth as canola protein is considered a valuable source of nutrition for livestock.

In terms of distribution channels, the market is divided into direct sales and indirect sales. The direct sales segment is expected to hold a significant market share as it enables manufacturers to establish direct relationships with customers and cater to their specific requirements. On the other hand, the indirect sales segment includes distribution through retailers, wholesalers, and e-commerce platforms, providing a wider reach to consumers globally.

